# Terraform Project: Modular AWS VPC and Subnets

This project sets up a repeatable AWS network layout using a custom local module. It creates one VPC and dynamically spins up multiple subnets based on a single configuration list.

* [ ] Set up the AWS provider configuration targeting the `ap-south-1` region.
* [ ] Create variables to accept configuration data for the VPC and a flexible list of subnets.
* [ ] Write a validation rule to check that all subnet CIDR blocks are typed correctly.
* [ ] Put the actual AWS resource code inside a separate `serviceroad` folder to keep it modular.
* [ ] Write code to create a single VPC using the input variables.
* [ ] Use a loop mechanism (`for_each`) to automatically generate a subnet resource for every item in my list.
* [ ] Link the generated subnets to the newly created VPC using its ID.
* [ ] Automatically tag each subnet using its unique map key name (`subnet_1`, `subnet_2`).
* [ ] Call the module from the root directory and pass the real IP ranges and names to deploy everything.

---

## Folder Structure

```text
.
└── highway
    ├── own_network_module.tf   # Where I call the module and pass input data
    ├── tera.tf                 # Cloud provider configuration (AWS)
    ├── terraform.tfstate       # State file generated by Terraform
    └── serviceroad
        ├── resource.tf         # Actual AWS resources being built (VPC, Subnets)
        └── variabl.tf          # Variable definitions and input validation rules

```

